                        "displayName": "Dewey Dunnington",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/Halifax"
                    },
                    "body": "Are there examples other than sf columns where this is relevant? It would be possible to make a generic list extension type that just calls {{serialize()}} on each element but it would probably be slow and we probably want to encourage other solutions. The other example I can think of is a list of models, maybe, for which the `broom::glance()` or `broom::tidy()` representation would fit in to Arrow format much better.",
